Hedge Funds Ownership
 Latest SEC 13F filings reveal 124 investment managers had shares of Hrg Group Inc. The institutional ownership of the firm in Q4 2014 is high, at 93.82% of the shares outstanding. They increased by 19.16 million the total shares they hold. As of that quarter these hedge funds owned 188.78 million shares. A total of 15 funds closed their positions in Hrg Group Inc and 35 reduced their holdings. There were 20 funds that created new positions and 39 funds that added to their positions. 
 As reported by SEC’s 13F filings, 11 hedge funds hold the stock in their Top 10 stock portfolios. Some of them are: Harbinger Capital Partners Ii Gp Llc, Harbinger Holdings Llc, Leucadia National Corp, Mittleman Brothers Llc, Js Capital Management Llc, Yost Capital Management L.L.C., Dynamo Internacional Gestao De Recursos Ltda., Fortress Investment Group Llc, Caspian Capital Lp, Covey Capital Advisors Llc.

 Goodhaven Capital Management Llc is the most positive institutional investor on Hrg Group Inc, with ownership of 695,100 shares as of Q4 2014 for 2.40% of the fund’s portfolio. Pecaut & Co. is another positive player having 173,700 shares of the company or 2.32% of their stocks portfolio. The stock is also 1.29% of the fund’s AUM. The New York-based fund Harbinger Capital Partners Ii Gp Llc have 100.00% of their stock portfolio invested in the stock for 3.36 million shares. In addition, The New York-based fund Harbinger Holdings Llc revealed it had purchased a stake worth 100.00% of the fund’s stock portfolio in the company. The New York-based fund Leucadia National Corp was also a notable believer in the publicly listed company, with ownership of 46.60 million shares. Hrg Group Inc is 98.47% of the fund’s stock portfolio.
HRG Group NYSE:HRG Company Profile
HRG Group, Inc., formerly Harbinger Group Inc., is a holding company. The Company’s operations are conducted through Fidelity & Guaranty Life (FGL), that offers life insurance and annuity products; Front Street Re (Delaware) Ltd. (Front Street), which offers reinsurance; Salus Capital Partners, LLC (Salus), Five Island Asset Management, LLC (FIAM), which holds interests in FIAM Capital Management, LLC (Five Island), Energy & Infrastructure Capital (EIC) and CorAmerica Capital, LLC (CorAmerica) offer financing and asset management, Spectrum Brands Holdings, Inc. (Spectrum Brands), which provides consumer products, such as batteries, small appliances, pet supplies, home and garden control products, personal care products and hardware and home improvement products. It also holds oil and natural gas properties through Compass Production GP, LLC and Compass Production Partners, LP. The Company operates through four segments: Consumer Products, Insurance, Energy and Asset Management.
Company Website: HRG Group
 The company has 13400 employees. Now its market capitalization is: $2.58 billion and it has 197.85 million shares outstanding. As of writing it has 94.30% shareholders and the institutional ownership stands at 94.30%. Hrg Group Inc was incorporated in Delaware on 2009-11-03. The stock closed at $13.12 yesterday and it had average 2 days volume of 994338 shares. It is up from the 30 days average shares volume of 862825. Hrg Group Inc has a 250 days low of $11.51 and a 52weeks high of $14.32. The current price is above the 200 days SMA.
